{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867600008,"sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","part":{"id":"prt_d79f51c850013ns3vNSF5pxaOc","messageID":"msg_d79f518a0001G4y36K70H217g6","sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867601686,"sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","part":{"id":"prt_d79f522f4001GoiSCcC5591sLh","messageID":"msg_d79f518a0001G4y36K70H217g6","sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-cf03a69eecb64fc58a5aced3e04881bc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document describes the implementation of four CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project. These binaries serve as the core executable components of the system, providing:\n6: \n7: 1. **agentd** - Kubernetes controller for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n8: 2. **picod** - HTTP server providing secure code interpreter execution environment\n9: 3. **workloadmanager** - RESTful API server for sandbox creation and session management\n10: 4. **agentcube-router** - Intelligent HTTP router for request routing and session management\n11: \n12: ## Background\n13: \n14: The AgentCube platform requires four distinct binary entry points to manage different aspects of the system:\n15: \n16: - **agentd**: Uses controller-runtime framework to reconcile Kubernetes custom resources\n17: - **picod**: Provides file management and code execution APIs within isolated workspace jails\n18: - **workloadmanager**: Manages sandbox pods, sessions, and resource allocation through REST APIs\n19: - **agentcube-router**: Routes HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n20: \n21: Currently, only `agentd` and `picod` binary entry points are implemented. This AR adds the remaining two entry points (`workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router`) and standardizes all four entry points with consistent patterns.\n22: \n23: ## Architecture\n24: \n25: ### Component Overview\n26: \n27: ```\n28: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n29: │                     Kubernetes Cluster                          │\n30: │                                                                  │\n31: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐│\n32: │  │     agentd       │  │ workloadmanager  │  │ agentcube-      ││\n33: │  │   (Controller)   │  │   (API Server)   │  │    router       ││\n34: │  │                  │  │                  │  │                 ││\n35: │  │ • Reconciler     │  │ • REST API       │  │ • HTTP Routing  ││\n36: │  │ • Leader Election│  │ • Session Mgmt   │  │ • JWT Auth      ││\n37: │  │ • Health Checks  │  │ • K8s Integration│  │ • Redis Store   ││\n38: │  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬────────┘│\n39: │           │                     │                     │          │\n40: │           ▼                     ▼                     ▼          │\n41: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n42: │  │                    Kubernetes API Server                   │ │\n43: │  │  • AgentRuntime CRD  • CodeInterpreter CRD  • Pods        │ │\n44: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                            │\n47:                            │\n48: ┌──────────────────────────▼─────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                    Sandbox Pods (PicoD Daemon)                 │\n50: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │                    picod (per pod)                       │  │\n52: │  │  • File Management API                                   │  │\n53: │  │  • Workspace Jail                                        │  │\n54: │  │  • JWT Authentication                                    │  │\n55: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n56: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Binary Entry Points\n60: \n61: | Binary | Path | Purpose | Package |\n62: |--------|------|---------|---------|\n63: | agentd | `cmd/agentd/` | Kubernetes controller | `pkg/agentd` |\n64: | picod | `cmd/picod/` | File management daemon | `pkg/picod` |\n65: | workloadmanager | `cmd/workloadmanager/` | Workload management API | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n66: | agentcube-router | `cmd/agentcube-router/` | HTTP routing proxy | `pkg/router` |\n67: \n68: ## Data Structures\n69: \n70: ### agentd Configuration\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: type Config struct {\n74:     MetricsAddr          string\n75:     ProbeAddr            string\n76:     EnableLeaderElection bool\n77:     LeaderElectionID     string\n78: }\n79: \n80: type Flags struct {\n81:     metricsBindAddress   string\n82:     healthProbeBindAddress string\n83:     leaderElect          bool\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### picod Configuration\n88: \n89: ```go\n90: type Config struct {\n91:     Port      int\n92:     Workspace string\n93: }\n94: \n95: type Flags struct {\n96:     port      int\n97:     workspace string\n98: }\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### workloadmanager Configuration\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: type Config struct {\n105:     Port              int\n106:     RedisAddr         string\n107:     RedisPassword     string\n108:     RedisDB           int\n109:     KubeconfigPath    string\n110:     MetricsAddr       string\n111:     ProbeAddr         string\n112:     EnableLeaderElection bool\n113: }\n114: \n115: type Flags struct {\n116:     port              string\n117:     redisAddr         string\n118:     redisPassword     string\n119:     redisDB           int\n120:     kubeconfig        string\n121:     metricsBindAddress string\n122:     healthProbeBindAddress string\n123:     leaderElect       bool\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ### agentcube-router Configuration\n128: \n129: ```go\n130: type Config struct {\n131:     Port                  int\n132:     WorkloadManagerURL    string\n133:     RedisAddr             string\n134:     RedisPassword         string\n135:     RedisDB               int\n136:     JWTSecretName         string\n137:     JWTTokenExpiration    time.Duration\n138:     RequireAuth           bool\n139:     MetricsAddr           string\n140: }\n141: \n142: type Flags struct {\n143:     port                  string\n144:     workloadManagerURL    string\n145:     redisAddr             string\n146:     redisPassword         string\n147:     redisDB               int\n148:     jwtSecretName         string\n149:     jwtTokenExpiration    string\n150:     requireAuth           bool\n151:     metricsBindAddress    string\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ## Implementation Details\n156: \n157: ### 1. agentd Binary Entry Point\n158: \n159: **File**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n160: \n161: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Kubernetes controller manager.\n162: \n163: **Implementation**:\n164: \n165: ```go\n166: func main() {\n167:     var metricsAddr string\n168:     var enableLeaderElection bool\n169:     var probeAddr string\n170: \n171:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n172:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to.\")\n173:     flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n174:         \"The address the probe endpoint binds to.\")\n175:     flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n176:         \"Enable leader election for controller manager.\")\n177: \n178:     opts := zap.Options{\n179:         Development: true,\n180:     }\n181:     opts.BindFlags(flag.CommandLine)\n182:     flag.Parse()\n183: \n184:     ctrl.SetLogger(zap.New(zap.UseFlagOptions(&opts)))\n185: \n186:     mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n187:         Scheme:                 scheme,\n188:         HealthProbeBindAddress: probeAddr,\n189:         LeaderElection:         enableLeaderElection,\n190:         LeaderElectionID:       \"agentd-leader\",\n191:     })\n192:     if err != nil {\n193:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to start manager\")\n194:         os.Exit(1)\n195:     }\n196: \n197:     if err = (&agentd.Reconciler{\n198:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n199:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n200:     }).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n201:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to create controller\", \"controller\", \"Agentd\")\n202:         os.Exit(1)\n203:     }\n204: \n205:     if err := mgr.AddHealthzCheck(\"healthz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n206:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up health check\")\n207:         os.Exit(1)\n208:     }\n209: \n210:     if err := mgr.AddReadyzCheck(\"readyz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n211:         setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up ready check\")\n212:         os.Exit(1)\n213:     }\n214: \n215:     setupLog.Info(\"starting manager\")\n216:     if err := mgr.Start(signals.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n217:         setupLog.Error(err, \"problem running manager\")\n218:         os.Exit(1)\n219:     }\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: **Key Features**:\n224: - Controller-runtime manager initialization\n225: - Reconciler registration for AgentRuntime resources\n226: - Health and readiness probe endpoints\n227: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n228: - Leader election support\n229: - Graceful shutdown handling\n230: \n231: ### 2. picod Binary Entry Point\n232: \n233: **File**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n234: \n235: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the PicoD HTTP server.\n236: \n237: **Implementation**:\n238: \n239: ```go\n240: func main() {\n241:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n242:     initFlags()\n243:     flag.Parse()\n244: \n245:     config := picod.Config{\n246:         Port:      GetPort(),\n247:         Workspace: GetWorkspace(),\n248:     }\n249: \n250:     server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n251:     if err != nil {\n252:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n253:     }\n254: \n255:     go func() {\n256:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n257:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n258:         }\n259:     }()\n260: \n261:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n262:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n263:     <-quit\n264: \n265:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n266:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n267:     defer cancel()\n268: \n269:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n270:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n271:     }\n272: \n273:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n274: }\n275: ```\n276: \n277: **Key Features**:\n278: - HTTP server initialization with configurable port\n279: - Workspace directory configuration\n280: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n281: - klog integration for logging\n282: \n283: ### 3. workloadmanager Binary Entry Point\n284: \n285: **File**: `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n286: \n287: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Workload Manager API server.\n288: \n289: **Implementation**:\n290: \n291: ```go\n292: func main() {\n293:     var port string\n294:     var redisAddr, redisPassword string\n295:     var redisDB int\n296:     var kubeconfig string\n297:     var metricsAddr, probeAddr string\n298:     var enableLeaderElection bool\n299: \n300:     flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n301:     flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n302:         \"Redis server address\")\n303:     flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n304:         \"Redis server password\")\n305:     flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n306:     flag.StringVar(&kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\",\n307:         \"Path to kubeconfig file (optional, in-cluster config if empty)\")\n308:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n309:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n310:     flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n311:         \"The address the probe endpoint binds to\")\n312:     flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n313:         \"Enable leader election\")\n314: \n315:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n316:     flag.Parse()\n317: \n318:     ctx := context.Background()\n319: \n320:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n321:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n322:         Password: redisPassword,\n323:         DB:       redisDB,\n324:     })\n325: \n326:     if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n327:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n328:     }\n329: \n330:     var kubeConfig *rest.Config\n331:     var err error\n332:     if kubeconfig != \"\" {\n333:         kubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n334:     } else {\n335:         kubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n336:     }\n337:     if err != nil {\n338:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n339:     }\n340: \n341:     clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n342:     if err != nil {\n343:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes clientset: %v\", err)\n344:     }\n345: \n346:     wmConfig := workloadmanager.Config{\n347:         Port:          port,\n348:         RedisClient:   redisClient,\n349:         K8sClient:     clientset,\n350:         MetricsAddr:   metricsAddr,\n351:         ProbeAddr:     probeAddr,\n352:     }\n353: \n354:     server, err := workloadmanager.NewServer(ctx, wmConfig)\n355:     if err != nil {\n356:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n357:     }\n358: \n359:     go func() {\n360:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n361:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n362:         }\n363:     }()\n364: \n365:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n366:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n367:     <-quit\n368: \n369:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n370:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n371:     defer cancel()\n372: \n373:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n374:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n375:     }\n376: \n377:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n378: }\n379: ```\n380: \n381: **Key Features**:\n382: - Redis client initialization with health check\n383: - Kubernetes client initialization (in-cluster or kubeconfig)\n384: - RESTful API server with configurable port\n385: - Health probe endpoints\n386: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n387: - Leader election support\n388: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n389: \n390: ### 4. agentcube-router Binary Entry Point\n391: \n392: **File**: `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n393: \n394: **Purpose**: Initialize and start the Router HTTP server.\n395: \n396: **Implementation**:\n397: \n398: ```go\n399: func main() {\n400:     var port string\n401:     var workloadManagerURL, redisAddr, redisPassword string\n402:     var redisDB int\n403:     var jwtSecretName, jwtTokenExpiration string\n404:     var requireAuth bool\n405:     var metricsAddr string\n406: \n407:     flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n408:     flag.StringVar(&workloadManagerURL, \"workload-manager-url\",\n409:         \"http://localhost:8080\", \"Workload manager URL\")\n410:     flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n411:         \"Redis server address\")\n412:     flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n413:         \"Redis server password\")\n414:     flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n415:     flag.StringVar(&jwtSecretName, \"jwt-secret-name\",\n416:         \"picod-router-identity\", \"Kubernetes secret name for JWT keys\")\n417:     flag.StringVar(&jwtTokenExpiration, \"jwt-token-expiration\", \"5m\",\n418:         \"JWT token expiration duration\")\n419:     flag.BoolVar(&requireAuth, \"require-auth\", false,\n420:         \"Require JWT authentication for all requests\")\n421:     flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n422:         \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n423: \n424:     klog.InitFlags(nil)\n425:     flag.Parse()\n426: \n427:     ctx := context.Background()\n428: \n429:     redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n430:         Addr:     redisAddr,\n431:         Password: redisPassword,\n432:         DB:       redisDB,\n433:     })\n434: \n435:     if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n436:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n437:     }\n438: \n439:     k8sConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n440:     if err != nil {\n441:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n442:     }\n443: \n444:     k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(k8sConfig)\n445:     if err != nil {\n446:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n447:     }\n448: \n449:     expiration, err := time.ParseDuration(jwtTokenExpiration)\n450:     if err != nil {\n451:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to parse JWT token expiration: %v\", err)\n452:     }\n453: \n454:     routerConfig := router.Config{\n455:         Port:               port,\n456:         WorkloadManagerURL: workloadManagerURL,\n457:         RedisClient:        redisClient,\n458:         K8sClient:          k8sClient,\n459:         JWTSecretName:      jwtSecretName,\n460:         JWTTokenExpiration: expiration,\n461:         RequireAuth:        requireAuth,\n462:         MetricsAddr:        metricsAddr,\n463:     }\n464: \n465:     server, err := router.NewServer(ctx, routerConfig)\n466:     if err != nil {\n467:         klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n468:     }\n469: \n470:     go func() {\n471:         if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n472:             klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n473:         }\n474:     }()\n475: \n476:     quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n477:     signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n478:     <-quit\n479: \n480:     klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n481:     ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n482:     defer cancel()\n483: \n484:     if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n485:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n486:     }\n487: \n488:     klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n489: }\n490: ```\n491: \n492: **Key Features**:\n493: - Redis client initialization for session storage\n494: - Kubernetes client for JWT secret access\n495: - Workload Manager client for proxying requests\n496: - JWT authentication/authorization\n497: - HTTP routing based on session IDs\n498: - Prometheus metrics endpoint\n499: - Graceful shutdown with timeout\n500: \n501: ## Error Handling\n502: \n503: ### Common Error Handling Patterns\n504: \n505: All binaries follow consistent error handling patterns:\n506: \n507: 1. **Fatal Errors**: Use `klog.Fatalf()` or `os.Exit(1)` for unrecoverable errors\n508: 2. **Graceful Shutdown**: Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM signals for clean shutdown\n509: 3. **Context Cancellation**: Use context with timeout for shutdown operations\n510: 4. **Health Checks**: Implement health and readiness probes for monitoring\n511: \n512: ### Startup Errors\n513: \n514: ```go\n515: // Example: Redis connection failure\n516: if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n517:     klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n518: }\n519: \n520: // Example: Kubernetes config failure\n521: kubeConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n522: if err != nil {\n523:     klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n524: }\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### Runtime Errors\n528: \n529: ```go\n530: // Example: Server runtime error\n531: go func() {\n532:     if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n533:         klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n534:     }\n535: }()\n536: \n537: // Example: Shutdown error\n538: if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n539:     klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n540: }\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ## Testing Strategy\n544: \n545: ### Unit Tests\n546: \n547: Each binary entry point should have unit tests covering:\n548: \n549: 1. **Flag Parsing**: Verify command-line flags are correctly parsed\n550: 2. **Configuration**: Verify configuration structs are correctly populated\n551: 3. **Initialization**: Verify dependencies (Redis, Kubernetes) are correctly initialized\n552: 4. **Error Handling**: Verify errors are properly handled and logged\n553: \n554: ### Integration Tests\n555: \n556: Integration tests should verify:\n557: \n558: 1. **End-to-End Startup**: Complete startup sequence with all dependencies\n559: 2. **Health Checks**: Health and readiness probes respond correctly\n560: 3. **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics are exposed correctly\n561: 4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Clean shutdown without resource leaks\n562: \n563: ### Test Structure\n564: \n565: ```\n566: cmd/agentd/\n567: ├── main.go\n568: └── main_test.go\n569: \n570: cmd/picod/\n571: ├── main.go\n572: └── main_test.go\n573: \n574: cmd/workloadmanager/\n575: ├── main.go\n576: └── main_test.go\n577: \n578: cmd/agentcube-router/\n579: ├── main.go\n580: └── main_test.go\n581: ```\n582: \n583: ## Build System\n584: \n585: ### Makefile Targets\n586: \n587: ```makefile\n588: # Build all binaries\n589: .PHONY: build\n590: build: build-agentd build-picod build-workloadmanager build-router\n591: \n592: # Build individual binaries\n593: .PHONY: build-agentd\n594: build-agentd:\n595: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n596: \t\t-o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n597: \n598: .PHONY: build-picod\n599: build-picod:\n600: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n601: \t\t-o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n602: \n603: .PHONY: build-workloadmanager\n604: build-workloadmanager:\n605: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n606: \t\t-o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n607: \n608: .PHONY: build-router\n609: build-router:\n610: \tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n611: \t\t-o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/agentcube-router\n612: \n613: # Clean build artifacts\n614: .PHONY: clean\n615: clean:\n616: \trm -rf bin/\n617: ```\n618: \n619: ### Build Optimization\n620: \n621: - **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binaries\n622: - **Strip Symbols**: `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to reduce binary size\n623: - **Version Injection**: `-X main.version=$(VERSION)` for version info\n624: \n625: ## Configuration\n626: \n627: ### Environment Variables\n628: \n629: All binaries support environment variable configuration in addition to flags:\n630: \n631: | Variable | Description | Default |\n632: |----------|-------------|---------|\n633: | `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | Metrics bind address for agentd | `:8080` |\n634: | `PICOD_PORT` | Port for picod server | `8080` |\n635: | `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | Workspace directory for picod | `/workspace` |\n636: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` | Port for workloadmanager | `8080` |\n637: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for workloadmanager | `localhost:6379` |\n638: | `ROUTER_PORT` | Port for router | `8080` |\n639: | `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager URL for router | `http://localhost:8080` |\n640: | `ROUTER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for router | `localhost:6379` |\n641: \n642: ### Kubernetes Deployment Configuration\n643: \n644: ```yaml\n645: apiVersion: apps/v1\n646: kind: Deployment\n647: metadata:\n648:   name: workloadmanager\n649:   namespace: agentcube\n650: spec:\n651:   replicas: 2\n652:   selector:\n653:     matchLabels:\n654:       app: workloadmanager\n655:   template:\n656:     metadata:\n657:       labels:\n658:         app: workloadmanager\n659:     spec:\n660:       containers:\n661:       - name: workloadmanager\n662:         image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n663:         ports:\n664:         - containerPort: 8080\n665:           name: http\n666:         - containerPort: 8081\n667:           name: health\n668:         - containerPort: 8080\n669:           name: metrics\n670:         env:\n671:         - name: PORT\n672:           value: \"8080\"\n673:         - name: REDIS_ADDR\n674:           valueFrom:\n675:             secretKeyRef:\n676:               name: redis-secret\n677:               key: address\n678:         - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n679:           valueFrom:\n680:             secretKeyRef:\n681:               name: redis-secret\n682:               key: password\n683:         livenessProbe:\n684:           httpGet:\n685:             path: /healthz\n686:             port: health\n687:         readinessProbe:\n688:           httpGet:\n689:             path: /readyz\n690:             port: health\n691:         resources:\n692:           requests:\n693:             cpu: 100m\n694:             memory: 128Mi\n695:           limits:\n696:             cpu: 500m\n697:             memory: 512Mi\n698: ```\n699: \n700: ## Monitoring and Observability\n701: \n702: ### Metrics\n703: \n704: All binaries expose Prometheus metrics on a dedicated port:\n705: \n706: - **agentd**: `:8080/metrics`\n707: - **picod**: `:8080/metrics` (if implemented)\n708: - **workloadmanager**: `:8080/metrics`\n709: - **agentcube-router**: `:8080/metrics`\n710: \n711: ### Health Checks\n712: \n713: | Binary | Health Endpoint | Ready Endpoint |\n714: |--------|-----------------|----------------|\n715: | agentd | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n716: | picod | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n717: | workloadmanager | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n718: | agentcube-router | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n719: \n720: ### Logging\n721: \n722: All binaries use `klog` for structured logging with consistent format:\n723: \n724: ```go\n725: klog.Info(\"Server started\")\n726: klog.Infof(\"Listening on port %d\", port)\n727: klog.Warningf(\"Connection failed: %v\", err)\n728: klog.Errorf(\"Fatal error: %v\", err)\n729: ```\n730: \n731: ## Dependencies\n732: \n733: ### Go Dependencies\n734: \n735: ```go\n736: import (\n737:     \"context\"\n738:     \"flag\"\n739:     \"os\"\n740:     \"os/signal\"\n741:     \"syscall\"\n742:     \"time\"\n743: \n744:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n745:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n746:     \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n747:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n748:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n749:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n750:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/healthz\"\n751:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log/zap\"\n752:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager/signals\"\n753: )\n754: ```\n755: \n756: ### Package Dependencies\n757: \n758: | Binary | Package | Purpose |\n759: |--------|---------|---------|\n760: | agentd | `pkg/agentd` | Controller logic |\n761: | picod | `pkg/picod` | Server logic |\n762: | workloadmanager | `pkg/workloadmanager` | API handlers |\n763: | agentcube-router | `pkg/router` | Routing logic |\n764: \n765: ## Security Considerations\n766: \n767: ### Authentication\n768: \n769: 1. **agentd**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n770: 2. **picod**: JWT-based authentication (optional)\n771: 3. **workloadmanager**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n772: 4. **agentcube-router**: JWT-based authentication with Kubernetes secret storage\n773: \n774: ### Authorization\n775: \n776: 1. **RBAC**: All binaries use Kubernetes RBAC for API access\n777: 2. **Secret Access**: Limited access to required secrets only\n778: 3. **Network Policies**: Restrict network access using Kubernetes network policies\n779: \n780: ### Secure Defaults\n781: \n782: - Use in-cluster configuration when running in Kubernetes\n783: - Require explicit kubeconfig for local development\n784: - Use strong default passwords for Redis (from secrets)\n785: - Enable TLS for production deployments\n786: \n787: ## Performance Considerations\n788: \n789: ### Resource Requirements\n790: \n791: | Binary | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n792: |--------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n793: | agentd | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n794: | picod | 100m | 500m | 64Mi | 256Mi |\n795: | workloadmanager | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n796: | agentcube-router | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n797: \n798: ### Optimization\n799: \n800: 1. **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for faster startup\n801: 2. **Binary Size**: Use `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to strip symbols\n802: 3. **Connection Pooling**: Redis and Kubernetes clients use connection pooling\n803: 4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Proper cleanup of resources on shutdown\n804: \n805: ## Deployment Strategy\n806: \n807: ### Phase 1: Development (Week 1)\n808: \n809: - Implement `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n810: - Implement `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n811: - Update Makefile with new build targets\n812: - Unit tests for new binaries\n813: \n814: ### Phase 2: Integration (Week 2)\n815: \n816: - Update Helm charts for new binaries\n817: - Configure RBAC permissions\n818: - Add health checks and probes\n819: - Integration tests\n820: \n821: ### Phase 3: Staging (Week 3)\n822: \n823: - Deploy to staging environment\n824: - Monitor metrics and logs\n825: - Performance testing\n826: - Security review\n827: \n828: ### Phase 4: Production (Week 4)\n829: \n830: - Deploy to production\n831: - Gradual rollout with feature flags\n832: - Monitor for issues\n833: - Full rollout\n834: \n835: ## References\n836: \n837: - controller-runtime documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\n838: - klog documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/klog/v2\n839: - Redis Go client: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n840: - Kubernetes client-go: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go\n841: \n842: ## Appendix A: Complete Binary Configuration\n843: \n844: ### agentd Flags\n845: \n846: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n847: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n848: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics endpoint address |\n849: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n850: | `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n851: \n852: ### picod Flags\n853: \n854: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n855: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n856: | `--port` | int | `8080` | Server port |\n857: | `--workspace` | string | `/workspace` | Workspace directory |\n858: \n859: ### workloadmanager Flags\n860: \n861: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n862: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n863: | `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n864: | `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n865: | `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n866: | `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n867: | `--kubeconfig` | string | `` | Kubeconfig path |\n868: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n869: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n870: | `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n871: \n872: ### agentcube-router Flags\n873: \n874: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n875: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n876: | `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n877: | `--workload-manager-url` | string | `http://localhost:8080` | Workload manager URL |\n878: | `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n879: | `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n880: | `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n881: | `--jwt-secret-name` | string | `picod-router-identity` | JWT secret name |\n882: | `--jwt-token-expiration` | string | `5m` | JWT token expiration |\n883: | `--require-auth` | bool | `false` | Require authentication |\n884: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n885: \n886: ## Appendix B: Startup Sequence Diagrams\n887: \n888: ### agentd Startup\n889: \n890: ```\n891: main()\n892: ├── Parse flags\n893: ├── Initialize logger (zap)\n894: ├── Create controller-runtime manager\n895: │   ├── Load kubeconfig\n896: │   ├── Create manager\n897: │   └── Set leader election config\n898: ├── Register reconciler\n899: ├── Add health checks\n900: │   ├── /healthz (liveness)\n901: │   └── /readyz (readiness)\n902: ├── Start manager\n903: │   ├── Leader election (if enabled)\n904: │   └── Start controllers\n905: └── Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n906:     └── Graceful shutdown\n907: ```\n908: \n909: ### workloadmanager Startup\n910: \n911: ```\n912: main()\n913: ├── Parse flags\n914: ├── Initialize logger (klog)\n915: ├── Connect to Redis\n916: │   └── Ping to verify connection\n917: ├── Create Kubernetes client\n918: │   ├── In-cluster config or kubeconfig\n919: │   └── Create clientset\n920: ├── Create server\n921: │   ├── Configure HTTP router\n922: │   ├── Register handlers\n923: │   └── Setup metrics\n924: ├── Start server (goroutine)\n925: ├── Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n926: └── Graceful shutdown\n927:     ├── Stop accepting new connections\n928:     ├── Wait for active connections (30s timeout)\n929:     └── Close Redis and Kubernetes clients\n930: ```\n\n(End of file - total 930 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019: CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries) Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document describes the implementation of four CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project. These binaries serve as the core executable components of the system, providing:\n\n1. **agentd** - Kubernetes controller for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **picod** - HTTP server providing secure code interpreter execution environment\n3. **workloadmanager** - RESTful API server for sandbox creation and session management\n4. **agentcube-router** - Intelligent HTTP router for request routing and session management\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube platform requires four distinct binary entry points to manage different aspects of the system:\n\n- **agentd**: Uses controller-runtime framework to reconcile Kubernetes custom resources\n- **picod**: Provides file management and code execution APIs within isolated workspace jails\n- **workloadmanager**: Manages sandbox pods, sessions, and resource allocation through REST APIs\n- **agentcube-router**: Routes HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md","time":{"start":1775867601676,"end":1775867601683}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775867601711,"sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","part":{"id":"prt_d79f523150014jBY6hkN3TiUAZ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79f518a0001G4y36K70H217g6","sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":44187,"input":234,"output":114,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":43839}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775867605548,"sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","part":{"id":"prt_d79f53229001jDD6U5oCeM0fhd","messageID":"msg_d79f5233d001PcOLjj8utbOZcl","sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867783919,"sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","part":{"id":"prt_d79f7e95b0017Q4bgtyrzc24ra","messageID":"msg_d79f5233d001PcOLjj8utbOZcl","sessionID":"ses_2860b7265ffe45JshERrf1yicI","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-59b098b08aa243d1bb5cbe6f6334cc6c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-022: CLI publish 命令 Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document describes the implementation of the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The publish command is responsible for deploying packaged agent workloads to either the AgentCube platform (using AgentRuntime custom resources) or standard Kubernetes (using Deployment and Service resources), including container image management and registry integration.\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI toolkit provides a comprehensive command-line interface for managing AI agent lifecycles. The publish command is a critical component that enables developers to deploy their agents to production environments. It supports two deployment targets:\n\n1. **AgentCube Provider**: Deploys agents using the AgentRuntime custom resource for enhanced features like session management and workload orchestration\n2. **Kubernetes Provider**: Deploys agents using standard Kubernetes Deployment and NodePort Service resources for broader compatibility\n\nThe publish command must handle various scenarios including:\n- Local image building and pushing to registries\n- Cloud-based image building\n- Image URL specification for pre-built images\n- Registry authentication\n- Version management\n- Deployment configuration (replicas, node ports, namespaces)\n- Provider-specific deployment strategies\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      CLI publish Command                        │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐│\n│  │ PublishRuntime   │  │  DockerService   │  │ MetadataService ││\n│  │                  │  │                  │  │                 ││\n│  │ • publish()      │  │ • push_image()   │  │ • load_metadata ││\n│  │ • _publish_cr()  │  │ • login()        │  │ • save_metadata ││\n│  │ • _publish_k8s() │  │ • tag_image()    │  │ • validate()    ││\n│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬────────┘│\n│           │                     │                     │          │\n│           ▼                     ▼                     ▼          │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                Provider Layer                              │ │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐              │ │\n│  │  │ AgentCubeProvider│  │ KubernetesProvider│              │ │\n│  │  │                  │  │                  │              │ │\n│  │  │ • deploy_agent_  │  │ • deploy_agent() │              │ │\n│  │  │   runtime()      │  │ • wait_for_      │              │ │\n│  │  │ • get_agent_     │  │   ready()        │              │ │\n│  │  │   runtime()      │  │ • delete_agent() │              │ │\n│  │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘              │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                            │\n                            ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Target Platform                             │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                Kubernetes Cluster                         │  │\n│  │  • AgentRuntime CRD (AgentCube provider)                  │  │\n│  │  • Deployment/Service (Kubernetes provider)               │  │\n│  │  • Pods with agent containers                             │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                Container Registry                         │  │\n│  │  • Docker Hub / Harbor / GCR / ACR                        │  │\n│  │  • Authentication and authorization                       │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Command Flow\n\n```\npublish(workspace, version, image_url, provider, ...options)\n│\n├─→ Load metadata from workspace\n│   └─→ Validate metadata and prerequisites\n│\n├─→ Prepare image for publishing\n│   ├─→ Local build mode:\n│   │   ├─→ Validate Docker availability\n│   │   ├─→ Build image (if needed)\n│   │   ├─→ Tag image with registry URL\n│   │   └─→ Push to registry with authentication\n│   │\n│   └─→ Cloud build mode:\n│       ├─→ Call cloud provider API\n│       └─→ Use returned image URL\n│\n├─→ Deploy based on provider\n│   ├─→ agentcube provider:\n│   │   ├─→ Validate router_url and workload_manager_url\n│   │   ├─→ Create AgentRuntime CR\n│   │   ├─→ Set session timeout (15m, 8h max)\n│   │   └─→ Return agent_id and endpoint\n│   │\n│   └─→ k8s provider:\n│       ├─→ Create Deployment\n│       ├─→ Create NodePort Service\n│       ├─→ Wait for rollout (120s timeout)\n│       ├─→ Get status and endpoints\n│       └─→ Handle readiness failures\n│\n├─→ Update metadata with deployment info\n│   └─→ Save agent_metadata.yaml\n│\n└─→ Display results to user\n    └─→ Show deployment URL, agent_id, status\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. Typer Command Interface\n\n**File**: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n\n**Purpose**: Define the publish command interface with all required options.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\n        \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n        help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n        show_default=True,\n    ),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--version\",\n        help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\",\n    ),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--image-url\",\n        help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\",\n    ),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--image-username\",\n        help=\"Username for image repository\",\n    ),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--image-password\",\n        help=\"Password for image repository\",\n    ),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--description\",\n        help=\"Agent description\",\n    ),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--region\",\n        help=\"Deployment region\",\n    ),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n        help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\",\n    ),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\n        \"agentcube\", \"--provider\",\n        help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\",\n    ),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--node-port\",\n        help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\",\n    ),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--replicas\",\n        help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\",\n    ),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n        None, \"--namespace\",\n        help=\"The namespace for the deployment\",\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n        False, \"--verbose\",\n        help=\"Enable detailed logging\",\n    ),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Publish and deploy an agent to AgentCube or Kubernetes.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n\n        with typer.progress(\n            tasks=[\n                (\"Loading workspace metadata\", \"load_metadata\"),\n                (\"Preparing image for publishing\", \"prepare_image\"),\n                (\"Deploying agent\", \"deploy\"),\n                (\"Updating metadata\", \"update_metadata\"),\n            ],\n        ) as progress:\n            metadata_path = runtime.publish(\n                workspace_path=Path(workspace),\n                version=version,\n                image_url=image_url,\n                image_username=image_username,\n                image_password=image_password,\n                description=description,\n                region=region,\n                cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n                provider=provider,\n                node_port=node_port,\n                replicas=replicas,\n                namespace=namespace,\n                progress=progress,\n            )\n\n        console.print(\n            f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent published successfully\",\n            f\"  Metadata: {metadata_path}\",\n        )\n\n    except Exception as e:\n        _handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Comprehensive option set for all publishing scenarios\n- Rich progress tracking with multiple tasks\n- Provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n- Registry authentication support\n- Kubernetes deployment customization (node_port, replicas, namespace)\n- Error handling with verbose mode\n\n### 2. PublishRuntime Class\n\n**File**: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n\n**Purpose**: Core publish logic orchestrating image preparation and deployment.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n        self.provider = provider\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=logging.DEBUG if verbose else logging.INFO)\n        self.metadata_service = MetadataService(verbose=verbose)\n        self.docker_service = DockerService(verbose=verbose)\n\n    def publish(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        **options: Any,\n    ) -> Path:\n        \"\"\"Publish an agent to the specified provider.\"\"\"\n        self.logger.info(f\"Publishing agent from {workspace_path}\")\n\n        # Load and validate metadata\n        metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n        # Apply option overrides\n        if options.get(\"description\"):\n            metadata.description = options[\"description\"]\n        if options.get(\"version\"):\n            metadata.version = options[\"version\"]\n        if options.get(\"region\"):\n            metadata.region = options[\"region\"]\n\n        # Prepare image for publishing\n        image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(\n            workspace_path,\n            metadata,\n            options,\n        )\n\n        # Deploy based on provider\n        if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n            agent_info = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(\n                workspace_path,\n                metadata,\n                image_url,\n                **options,\n            )\n        else:\n            agent_info = self._publish_k8s(\n                workspace_path,\n                metadata,\n                image_url,\n                **options,\n            )\n\n        # Update metadata with deployment info\n        self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n\n        return workspace_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        options: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare and push image to registry.\"\"\"\n        if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n            return self._prepare_local_image(\n                workspace_path,\n                metadata,\n                options,\n            )\n        else:\n            return self._prepare_cloud_image(\n                workspace_path,\n                metadata,\n                options,\n            )\n\n    def _prepare_local_image(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        options: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare local image by pushing to registry.\"\"\"\n        # Validate Docker is available\n        if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n            raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n\n        # Get image URL from options or metadata\n        image_url = options.get(\"image_url\") or metadata.image_url\n        if not image_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"Image URL is required for local build mode. \"\n                \"Use --image-url or set image_url in metadata.\"\n            )\n\n        # Build local image name\n        local_image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:latest\"\n\n        # Tag image for registry\n        registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n        registry_username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n        registry_password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n\n        self.logger.info(f\"Tagging image {local_image_name} -> {image_url}\")\n        self.docker_service._tag_image_sdk(local_image_name, image_url)\n\n        # Push to registry\n        self.logger.info(f\"Pushing image to registry: {image_url}\")\n        push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n            image_name=image_url,\n            registry_url=registry_url,\n            username=registry_username,\n            password=registry_password,\n        )\n\n        self.logger.info(f\"Image pushed successfully: {push_result['pushed_image']}\")\n        return push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        options: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Prepare cloud image by calling cloud provider API.\"\"\"\n        cloud_provider = options.get(\"cloud_provider\") or metadata.cloud_provider\n        if not cloud_provider:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"Cloud provider is required for cloud build mode. \"\n                \"Use --cloud-provider or set cloud_provider in metadata.\"\n            )\n\n        # Call cloud provider build API\n        self.logger.info(f\"Building image in cloud: {cloud_provider}\")\n\n        # Placeholder for cloud provider integration\n        # This would call the appropriate cloud provider API\n        # For now, raise NotImplementedError\n        raise NotImplementedError(\n            f\"Cloud build mode for provider '{cloud_provider}' is not yet implemented\"\n        )\n\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        image_url: str,\n        **options: Any,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish agent using AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR).\"\"\"\n        from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n\n        # Validate required fields\n        if not metadata.router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"router_url is required for agentcube provider. \"\n                \"Set it in agent_metadata.yaml.\"\n            )\n        if not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"workload_manager_url is required for agentcube provider. \"\n                \"Set it in agent_metadata.yaml.\"\n            )\n\n        namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n        provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n            namespace=namespace,\n            verbose=self.verbose,\n        )\n\n        # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n        self.logger.info(f\"Deploying AgentRuntime CR for {metadata.agent_name}\")\n\n        deploy_result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n            agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=metadata.port,\n            entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n            env_vars={\n                \"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\": metadata.workload_manager_url,\n                \"ROUTER_URL\": metadata.router_url,\n            },\n            workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n            router_url=metadata.router_url,\n            readiness_probe_path=metadata.readiness_probe_path or \"/health\",\n            readiness_probe_port=metadata.readiness_probe_port or metadata.port,\n        )\n\n        self.logger.info(f\"AgentRuntime CR deployed: {deploy_result}\")\n\n        return {\n            \"agent_id\": deploy_result.get(\"agent_id\"),\n            \"agent_endpoint\": deploy_result.get(\"agent_endpoint\"),\n            \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n        }\n\n    def _publish_k8s(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        metadata: AgentMetadata,\n        image_url: str,\n        **options: Any,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Publish agent using standard Kubernetes provider.\"\"\"\n        from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n\n        namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n        replicas = options.get(\"replicas\") or 1\n        node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n\n        provider = KubernetesProvider(\n            namespace=namespace,\n            verbose=self.verbose,\n        )\n\n        # Deploy using standard Kubernetes resources\n        self.logger.info(f\"Deploying agent {metadata.agent_name} to Kubernetes\")\n\n        deploy_result = provider.deploy_agent(\n            agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=metadata.port,\n            entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n            replicas=replicas,\n            node_port=node_port,\n            env_vars={\n                \"PORT\": str(metadata.port),\n            },\n        )\n\n        self.logger.info(f\"Agent deployed: {deploy_result}\")\n\n        return {\n            \"deployment_name\": deploy_result[\"deployment_name\"],\n            \"service_name\": deploy_result[\"service_name\"],\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"service_url\": deploy_result[\"service_url\"],\n            \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n            \"replicas\": replicas,\n            \"node_port\": deploy_result.get(\"node_port\"),\n            \"image_url\": image_url,\n        }\n\n    def _update_publish_metadata(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        agent_info: Dict[str, Any],\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Update metadata with deployment information.\"\"\"\n        metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n        # Update deployment-specific fields\n        if agent_info[\"provider\"] == \"agentcube\":\n            metadata.agent_id = agent_info[\"agent_id\"]\n            metadata.agent_endpoint = agent_info[\"agent_endpoint\"]\n        else:\n            metadata.k8s_deployment = {\n                \"deployment_name\": agent_info[\"deployment_name\"],\n                \"service_name\": agent_info[\"service_name\"],\n                \"service_url\": agent_info[\"service_url\"],\n                \"replicas\": agent_info[\"replicas\"],\n                \"node_port\": agent_info.get(\"node_port\"),\n            }\n\n        # Update common fields\n        metadata.image_url = agent_info[\"image_url\"]\n\n        # Save updated metadata\n        self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n\n        self.logger.info(f\"Updated metadata at {workspace_path}/agent_metadata.yaml\")\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Provider abstraction (agentcube/k8s)\n- Image preparation and registry push\n- CR deployment for AgentCube provider\n- Standard K8s deployment for k8s provider\n- Metadata updates with deployment info\n- Comprehensive error handling\n- Progress tracking support\n\n### 3. DockerService Integration\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n\n**Purpose**: Handle Docker operations for image tagging and pushing.\n\n**Enhanced Methods**:\n\n```python\ndef _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Login to Docker registry using SDK.\"\"\"\n    client = docker.from_env()\n    try:\n        if registry:\n            client.login(username=username, password=password, registry=registry)\n        else:\n            client.login(username=username, password=password)\n        self.logger.info(f\"Successfully logged in to registry: {registry or 'Docker Hub'}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Failed to login to registry: {e}\")\n        raise\n\ndef _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Tag Docker image using SDK.\"\"\"\n    client = docker.from_env()\n    try:\n        image = client.images.get(source_image)\n        image.tag(target_image)\n        self.logger.info(f\"Tagged image: {source_image} -> {target_image}\")\n    except docker.errors.ImageNotFound:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Image not found: {source_image}\")\n        raise\n    except Exception as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Failed to tag image: {e}\")\n        raise\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Registry authentication\n- Image tagging for registry\n- Error handling and logging\n- SDK-based operations\n\n### 4. AgentCubeProvider Integration\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n\n**Purpose**: Deploy agents using AgentRuntime custom resources.\n\n**Enhanced Methods**:\n\n```python\ndef deploy_agent_runtime(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Deploy agent using AgentRuntime custom resource.\"\"\"\n    sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n    # Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n    agent_runtime = {\n        \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n        \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n        \"metadata\": {\n            \"name\": sanitized_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n        },\n        \"spec\": {\n            \"agentName\": agent_name,\n            \"image\": image_url,\n            \"port\": port,\n            \"entrypoint\": entrypoint or \"\",\n            \"env\": env_vars or {},\n            \"sessionTimeout\": \"15m\",\n            \"maxSessionDuration\": \"8h\",\n            \"imagePullSecrets\": [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}],\n        },\n    }\n\n    # Add readiness probe if provided\n    if readiness_probe_path and readiness_probe_port:\n        agent_runtime[\"spec\"][\"readinessProbe\"] = {\n            \"httpGet\": {\n                \"path\": readiness_probe_path,\n                \"port\": readiness_probe_port,\n            },\n            \"initialDelaySeconds\": 10,\n            \"periodSeconds\": 10,\n        }\n\n    # Create or update CR\n    try:\n        self.custom_objects_api.create_namespaced_custom_object(\n            group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n            version=\"v1alpha1\",\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n            plural=\"agentruntimes\",\n            body=agent_runtime,\n        )\n        self.logger.info(f\"Created AgentRuntime CR: {sanitized_name}\")\n    except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n        if e.status == 409:\n            # CR already exists, update it\n            self.custom_objects_api.patch_namespaced_custom_object(\n                group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n                version=\"v1alpha1\",\n                namespace=self.namespace,\n                plural=\"agentruntimes\",\n                name=sanitized_name,\n                body=agent_runtime,\n            )\n            self.logger.info(f\"Updated AgentRuntime CR: {sanitized_name}\")\n        else:\n            raise\n\n    # Return deployment info\n    return {\n        \"agent_id\": sanitized_name,\n        \"agent_endpoint\": f\"{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{self.namespace}/agent-runtimes/{sanitized_name}\",\n    }\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- AgentRuntime CR creation/update\n- Readiness probe configuration\n- Session timeout settings\n- Image pull secrets\n- Environment variable injection\n\n### 5. KubernetesProvider Integration\n\n**File**: `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n\n**Purpose**: Deploy agents using standard Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Enhanced Methods**:\n\n```python\ndef wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Wait for deployment to be ready with timeout.\"\"\"\n    start_time = time.time()\n\n    while time.time() - start_time < timeout:\n        deployment = self.apps_v1.read_namespaced_deployment(\n            name=name,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n        )\n\n        if deployment.status.ready_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas:\n            self.logger.info(f\"Deployment {name} is ready\")\n            return\n\n        time.sleep(5)\n\n    raise TimeoutError(\n        f\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\"\n    )\n\ndef deploy_agent(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    replicas: int = 1,\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Deploy agent using Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n    sanitized_name = self._sanitize_name(agent_name)\n\n    # Create Deployment\n    deployment = self._create_deployment(\n        name=sanitized_name,\n        image_url=image_url,\n        port=port,\n        entrypoint=entrypoint,\n        replicas=replicas,\n        env_vars=env_vars,\n    )\n\n    self.logger.info(f\"Created Deployment: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n    # Create Service\n    service = self._create_service(\n        name=sanitized_name,\n        port=port,\n        node_port=node_port,\n    )\n\n    self.logger.info(f\"Created Service: {sanitized_name}\")\n\n    # Wait for deployment to be ready\n    try:\n        self.wait_for_deployment_ready(sanitized_name)\n    except TimeoutError as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Deployment readiness check failed: {e}\")\n        # Log error in metadata but don't fail the command\n        raise\n\n    # Get service URL\n    service_url = f\"http://localhost:{service.spec.ports[0].node_port}\"\n\n    return {\n        \"deployment_name\": sanitized_name,\n        \"service_name\": sanitized_name,\n        \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n        \"replicas\": replicas,\n        \"container_port\": port,\n        \"node_port\": service.spec.ports[0].node_port,\n        \"service_url\": service_url,\n    }\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Deployment and Service creation\n- Readiness waiting with timeout\n- NodePort configuration\n- Environment variable support\n- Error handling for readiness failures\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Publish Options\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass PublishOptions:\n    \"\"\"Options for the publish command.\"\"\"\n    workspace: str = \".\"\n    version: Optional[str] = None\n    image_url: Optional[str] = None\n    image_username: Optional[str] = None\n    image_password: Optional[str] = None\n    description: Optional[str] = None\n    region: Optional[str] = None\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None\n    replicas: Optional[int] = None\n    namespace: Optional[str] = None\n    verbose: bool = False\n\n    @classmethod\n    def from_dict(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"PublishOptions\":\n        \"\"\"Create PublishOptions from dictionary.\"\"\"\n        return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if k in cls.__annotations__})\n```\n\n### Deployment Result\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass DeploymentResult:\n    \"\"\"Result of a deployment operation.\"\"\"\n    agent_id: Optional[str] = None  # AgentCube provider\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None  # AgentCube provider\n    deployment_name: Optional[str] = None  # K8s provider\n    service_name: Optional[str] = None  # K8s provider\n    service_url: Optional[str] = None  # K8s provider\n    namespace: str = \"default\"\n    provider: str = \"agentcube\"\n    replicas: Optional[int] = None  # K8s provider\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None  # K8s provider\n    image_url: str = \"\"\n    status: str = \"deployed\"\n    error: Optional[str] = None\n\n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n        \"\"\"Convert to dictionary.\"\"\"\n        return asdict(self)\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Spec\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass AgentRuntimeSpec:\n    \"\"\"Specification for AgentRuntime custom resource.\"\"\"\n    agentName: str\n    image: str\n    port: int\n    entrypoint: str = \"\"\n    env: Dict[str, str] = field(default_factory=dict)\n    sessionTimeout: str = \"15m\"\n    maxSessionDuration: str = \"8h\"\n    imagePullSecrets: List[Dict[str, str]] = field(\n        default_factory=lambda: [{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]\n    )\n    readinessProbe: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Common Error Scenarios\n\n```python\nclass PublishError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for publish operations.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass ImagePreparationError(PublishError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when image preparation fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass RegistryAuthenticationError(PublishError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when registry authentication fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DeploymentError(PublishError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when deployment fails.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass ReadinessTimeoutError(DeploymentError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when deployment readiness times out.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass PrerequisitesError(PublishError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when prerequisites are not met.\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### Error Handling in PublishRuntime\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_local_image(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    options: Dict[str, Any],\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Prepare local image by pushing to registry.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Validate Docker is available\n        if not self.docker_service.check_docker_available():\n            raise PrerequisitesError(\n                \"Docker is not available or not running. \"\n                \"Please ensure Docker is installed and running.\"\n            )\n\n        # Get image URL\n        image_url = options.get(\"image_url\") or metadata.image_url\n        if not image_url:\n            raise ImagePreparationError(\n                \"Image URL is required for local build mode. \"\n                \"Use --image-url or set image_url in metadata.\"\n            )\n\n        # Tag and push image\n        local_image_name = f\"{metadata.agent_name}:latest\"\n        self.docker_service._tag_image_sdk(local_image_name, image_url)\n\n        try:\n            push_result = self.docker_service.push_image(\n                image_name=image_url,\n                registry_url=options.get(\"registry_url\"),\n                username=options.get(\"image_username\"),\n                password=options.get(\"image_password\"),\n            )\n        except Exception as e:\n            raise RegistryAuthenticationError(\n                f\"Failed to push image to registry: {e}\"\n            )\n\n        return push_result[\"pushed_image\"]\n\n    except PrerequisitesError:\n        raise\n    except ImagePreparationError:\n        raise\n    except RegistryAuthenticationError:\n        raise\n    except Exception as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Unexpected error during image preparation: {e}\")\n        raise ImagePreparationError(f\"Failed to prepare image: {e}\")\n```\n\n### Error Handling in Deployment\n\n```python\ndef _publish_k8s(\n    self,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n    metadata: AgentMetadata,\n    image_url: str,\n    **options: Any,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Publish agent using standard Kubernetes provider.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        provider = KubernetesProvider(\n            namespace=options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\",\n            verbose=self.verbose,\n        )\n\n        deploy_result = provider.deploy_agent(\n            agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n            image_url=image_url,\n            port=metadata.port,\n            entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n            replicas=options.get(\"replicas\") or 1,\n            node_port=options.get(\"node_port\"),\n        )\n\n        return deploy_result\n\n    except TimeoutError as e:\n        # Log error in metadata but still return result\n        self.logger.error(f\"Deployment readiness check timed out: {e}\")\n        return {\n            **deploy_result,\n            \"status\": \"readiness_timeout\",\n            \"error\": str(e),\n        }\n    except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n        raise DeploymentError(f\"Kubernetes API error: {e}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        self.logger.error(f\"Unexpected error during deployment: {e}\")\n        raise DeploymentError(f\"Failed to deploy agent: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py`\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\nfrom agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\nfrom agentcube.models.pack_models import AgentMetadata\n\nclass TestPublishRuntime:\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def runtime(self):\n        return PublishRuntime(verbose=True, provider=\"agentcube\")\n\n    @pytest.fixture\n    def sample_metadata(self):\n        return AgentMetadata(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            language=\"python\",\n            entrypoint=\"python main.py\",\n            port=8080,\n            build_mode=\"local\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            workload_manager_url=\"http://wm:8080\",\n        )\n\n    def test_init(self, runtime):\n        assert runtime.verbose is True\n        assert runtime.provider == \"agentcube\"\n        assert runtime.metadata_service is not None\n        assert runtime.docker_service is not None\n\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image\")\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._publish_cr_to_k8s\")\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata\")\n    def test_publish_agentcube_provider(\n        self,\n        mock_update,\n        mock_publish_cr,\n        mock_prepare_image,\n        runtime,\n        sample_metadata,\n        tmp_path,\n    ):\n        # Setup mocks\n        mock_prepare_image.return_value = \"registry.example.com/test-agent:v1.0.0\"\n        mock_publish_cr.return_value = {\n            \"agent_id\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://router:8080/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/test-agent\",\n            \"provider\": \"agentcube\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"image_url\": \"registry.example.com/test-agent:v1.0.0\",\n        }\n\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.metadata_service,\n            \"load_metadata\",\n            return_value=sample_metadata,\n        ):\n            result = runtime.publish(\n                workspace_path=tmp_path,\n                version=\"v1.0.0\",\n            )\n\n        assert result == tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        mock_prepare_image.assert_called_once()\n        mock_publish_cr.assert_called_once()\n        mock_update.assert_called_once()\n\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image\")\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._publish_k8s\")\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._update_publish_metadata\")\n    def test_publish_k8s_provider(\n        self,\n        mock_update,\n        mock_publish_k8s,\n        mock_prepare_image,\n        sample_metadata,\n        tmp_path,\n    ):\n        runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"k8s\")\n\n        # Setup mocks\n        mock_prepare_image.return_value = \"registry.example.com/test-agent:v1.0.0\"\n        mock_publish_k8s.return_value = {\n            \"deployment_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"service_name\": \"test-agent\",\n            \"namespace\": \"default\",\n            \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30001\",\n            \"provider\": \"k8s\",\n            \"replicas\": 2,\n            \"node_port\": 30001,\n            \"image_url\": \"registry.example.com/test-agent:v1.0.0\",\n        }\n\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.metadata_service,\n            \"load_metadata\",\n            return_value=sample_metadata,\n        ):\n            result = runtime.publish(\n                workspace_path=tmp_path,\n                replicas=2,\n            )\n\n        assert result == tmp_path / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        mock_prepare_image.assert_called_once()\n        mock_publish_k8s.assert_called_once()\n\n    def test_prepare_local_image_docker_unavailable(self, runtime, sample_metadata):\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.docker_service,\n            \"check_docker_available\",\n            return_value=False,\n        ):\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError) as exc_info:\n                runtime._prepare_local_image(\n                    Path(\"/tmp\"),\n                    sample_metadata,\n                    {\"image_url\": \"registry.example.com/test:v1\"},\n                )\n\n            assert \"Docker is not available\" in str(exc_info.value)\n\n    def test_prepare_local_image_missing_image_url(self, runtime, sample_metadata):\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.docker_service,\n            \"check_docker_available\",\n            return_value=True,\n        ):\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n                runtime._prepare_local_image(\n                    Path(\"/tmp\"),\n                    sample_metadata,\n                    {},\n                )\n\n            assert \"Image URL is required\" in str(exc_info.value)\n\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image\")\n    def test_publish_cr_to_k8s_missing_router_url(\n        self,\n        mock_prepare_image,\n        runtime,\n        sample_metadata,\n        tmp_path,\n    ):\n        sample_metadata.router_url = None\n\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.metadata_service,\n            \"load_metadata\",\n            return_value=sample_metadata,\n        ):\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n                runtime._publish_cr_to_k8s(\n                    tmp_path,\n                    sample_metadata,\n                    \"registry.example.com/test:v1\",\n                )\n\n            assert \"router_url is required\" in str(exc_info.value)\n\n    @patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image\")\n    def test_publish_cr_to_k8s_missing_workload_manager_url(\n        self,\n        mock_prepare_image,\n        runtime,\n        sample_metadata,\n        tmp_path,\n    ):\n        sample_metadata.workload_manager_url = None\n\n        with patch.object(\n            runtime.metadata_service,\n            \"load_metadata\",\n            return_value=sample_metadata,\n        ):\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError) as exc_info:\n                runtime._publish_cr_to_k8s(\n                    tmp_path,\n                    sample_metadata,\n                    \"registry.example.com/test:v1\",\n                )\n\n            assert \"workload_manager_url is required\" in str(exc_info.value)\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n**File**: `tests/integration/test_publish_command.py`\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport subprocess\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\nclass TestPublishCommandIntegration:\n    def test_publish_local_image_to_registry(\n        self,\n        sample_agent_workspace: Path,\n        docker_registry_url: str,\n        registry_credentials: tuple,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Test publishing a local image to a Docker registry.\"\"\"\n        workspace = sample_agent_workspace\n\n        # Build the agent first\n        subprocess.run(\n            [\"kubectl-agentcube\", \"build\", \"-f\", str(workspace)],\n            check=True,\n        )\n\n        # Publish to registry\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"kubectl-agentcube\", \"publish\",\n                \"-f\", str(workspace),\n                \"--image-url\", f\"{docker_registry_url}/test-agent:v1.0.0\",\n                \"--image-username\", registry_credentials[0],\n                \"--image-password\", registry_credentials[1],\n                \"--provider\", \"k8s\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n\n        assert result.returncode == 0\n        assert \"Agent published successfully\" in result.stdout\n\n    @pytest.mark.k8s\n    def test_publish_to_kubernetes(\n        self,\n        sample_agent_workspace: Path,\n        k8s_namespace: str,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Test publishing to Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n        workspace = sample_agent_workspace\n\n        # Publish to Kubernetes\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"kubectl-agentcube\", \"publish\",\n                \"-f\", str(workspace),\n                \"--namespace\", k8s_namespace,\n                \"--provider\", \"k8s\",\n                \"--replicas\", \"2\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n\n        assert result.returncode == 0\n\n        # Verify deployment exists\n        check_result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"kubectl\", \"get\", \"deployment\",\n                \"-n\", k8s_namespace,\n                \"test-agent\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n\n        assert check_result.returncode == 0\n\n    @pytest.mark.agentcube\n    def test_publish_to_agentcube_provider(\n        self,\n        sample_agent_workspace: Path,\n        agentcube_namespace: str,\n        router_url: str,\n        workload_manager_url: str,\n    ):\n        \"\"\"Test publishing to AgentCube provider.\"\"\"\n        workspace = sample_agent_workspace\n\n        # Update metadata with required URLs\n        metadata_file = workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n        with open(metadata_file) as f:\n            metadata_content = f.read()\n        metadata_content = metadata_content.replace(\n            \"router_url: \\\"\\\"\",\n            f'router_url: \"{router_url}\"'\n        )\n        metadata_content = metadata_content.replace(\n            \"workload_manager_url: \\\"\\\"\",\n            f'workload_manager_url: \"{workload_manager_url}\"'\n        )\n        with open(metadata_file, \"w\") as f:\n            f.write(metadata_content)\n\n        # Publish to AgentCube\n        result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"kubectl-agentcube\", \"publish\",\n                \"-f\", str(workspace),\n                \"--namespace\", agentcube_namespace,\n                \"--provider\", \"agentcube\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n\n        assert result.returncode == 0\n\n        # Verify AgentRuntime CR exists\n        check_result = subprocess.run(\n            [\n                \"kubectl\", \"get\", \"agentruntime\",\n                \"-n\", agentcube_namespace,\n                \"test-agent\",\n            ],\n            capture_output=True,\n            text=True,\n        )\n\n        assert check_result.returncode == 0\n```\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n**File**: `tests/conftest.py`\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport tempfile\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef sample_agent_workspace():\n    \"\"\"Create a sample agent workspace for testing.\"\"\"\n    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:\n        workspace = Path(tmpdir)\n\n        # Create directory structure\n        (workspace / \"src\").mkdir()\n\n        # Create main.py\n        (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text(\"\"\"\nimport os\nfrom http.server import HTTPServer, BaseHTTPRequestHandler\n\nclass AgentHandler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):\n    def do_POST(self):\n        content_length = int(self.headers['Content-Length'])\n        post_data = self.rfile.read(content_length)\n        self.send_response(200)\n        self.send_header('Content-type', 'application/json')\n        self.end_headers()\n        self.wfile.write(b'{\"result\": \"success\"}')\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    port = int(os.environ.get('PORT', 8080))\n    server = HTTPServer(('0.0.0.0', port), AgentHandler)\n    server.serve_forever()\n\"\"\")\n\n        # Create requirements.txt\n        (workspace / \"requirements.txt\").write_text(\"\")\n\n        # Create agent_metadata.yaml\n        (workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\"\"\"\nagent_name: test-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\nrouter_url: \"\"\nworkload_manager_url: \"\"\n\"\"\")\n\n        yield workspace\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef docker_registry_url():\n    \"\"\"Docker registry URL for testing.\"\"\"\n    return \"localhost:5000\"\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef registry_credentials():\n    \"\"\"Docker registry credentials for testing.\"\"\"\n    return (\"testuser\", \"testpass\")\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef k8s_namespace():\n    \"\"\"Kubernetes namespace for testing.\"\"\"\n    return \"agentcube-test\"\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef agentcube_namespace():\n    \"\"\"AgentCube namespace for testing.\"\"\"\n    return \"agentcube-system\"\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef router_url():\n    \"\"\"Router URL for testing.\"\"\"\n    return \"http://agentcube-router:8080\"\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workload_manager_url():\n    \"\"\"Workload Manager URL for testing.\"\"\"\n    return \"http://workloadmanager:8080\"\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL` | Default Docker registry URL | None |\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME` | Default registry username | None |\n| `DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD` | Default registry password | None |\n| `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file path | `~/.kube/config` |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube Router URL | None |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload Manager URL | None |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | Default AgentCube namespace | `agentcube-system` |\n| `K8S_NAMESPACE` | Default Kubernetes namespace | `default` |\n\n### Configuration File\n\n```yaml\n# ~/.agentcube/config.yaml\npublish:\n  defaults:\n    provider: agentcube\n    namespace: default\n    replicas: 1\n\n  registry:\n    url: registry.example.com\n    username: ${DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME}\n    password: ${DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD}\n\n  agentcube:\n    router_url: http://agentcube-router:8080\n    workload_manager_url: http://workloadmanager:8080\n    readiness_probe_path: /health\n    readiness_probe_port: 8080\n\n  kubernetes:\n    node_port_range:\n      min: 30000\n      max: 32767\n    readiness_timeout: 120\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Python Dependencies\n\n```toml\n[tool.poetry.dependencies]\npython = \"^3.10\"\ntyper = {extras = [\"all\"], version = \"^0.9.0\"}\npydantic = \"^2.0.0\"\npyyaml = \"^6.0\"\nhttpx = \"^0.24.0\"\ndocker = \"^6.0.0\"\nrich = \"^13.0.0\"\npackaging = \"^23.0\"\nimportlib-resources = \"^6.0.0\"\nsemver = \"^3.0.0\"\nkubernetes = \"^28.0.0\"\n\n[tool.poetry.group.dev.dependencies]\npytest = \"^7.4.0\"\npytest-asyncio = \"^0.21.0\"\npytest-cov = \"^4.1.0\"\npytest-mock = \"^3.11.0\"\nhttpx-mock = \"^0.10.0\"\nruff = \"^0.1.0\"\nmypy = \"^1.5.0\"\npre-commit = \"^3.3.0\"\n```\n\n### External Services\n\n1. **Docker Daemon**: Required for local image operations\n2. **Container Registry**: For image storage and distribution\n3. **Kubernetes Cluster**: For deployment target\n4. **AgentCube Platform**: For AgentRuntime CR management\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Registry Authentication\n\n1. **Credential Storage**: Never log registry credentials\n2. **Environment Variables**: Use environment variables for sensitive data\n3. **Secret Management**: Integrate with Kubernetes secrets when possible\n4. **Token Refresh**: Support for token-based authentication refresh\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube-publisher\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"namespaces\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"apps\"]\n  resources: [\"deployments\", \"services\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n### Network Security\n\n1. **TLS/SSL**: Use secure connections for registry access\n2. **Internal Registries**: Support for private/internal registries\n3. **Network Policies**: Respect Kubernetes network policies\n4. **Firewall Rules**: Ensure required ports are accessible\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Image Push Optimization\n\n1. **Layer Caching**: Leverage Docker layer caching\n2. **Parallel Uploads**: Use parallel layer uploads when supported\n3. **Compression**: Enable image compression\n4. **Registry Mirrors**: Use registry mirrors for faster access\n\n### Deployment Performance\n\n1. **Resource Limits**: Set appropriate resource limits\n2. **Readiness Probes**: Configure efficient readiness probes\n3. **Rollout Strategy**: Use appropriate rollout strategies\n4. **Connection Pooling**: Reuse Kubernetes API connections\n\n### Memory Usage\n\n| Operation | Estimated Memory Usage |\n|-----------|------------------------|\n| Image tagging | ~50 MB |\n| Image push | ~100 MB |\n| CR creation | ~20 MB |\n| K8s deployment | ~30 MB |\n| Total | ~200 MB |\n\n## Deployment Strategy\n\n### Phase 1: Core Implementation (Week 1)\n\n- Implement `PublishRuntime` class\n- Implement local image preparation\n- Implement AgentCube provider deployment\n- Unit tests for core functionality\n\n### Phase 2: Kubernetes Provider (Week 2)\n\n- Implement Kubernetes provider deployment\n- Implement readiness waiting\n- Implement error handling\n- Integration tests for K8s provider\n\n### Phase 3: Registry Integration (Week 3)\n\n- Implement Docker SDK integration\n- Implement registry authentication\n- Implement error handling for registry operations\n- Tests for various registry scenarios\n\n### Phase 4: Cloud Provider Support (Week 4)\n\n- Implement cloud provider integration\n- Add cloud provider-specific logic\n- Documentation for cloud deployment\n- End-to-end testing\n\n### Phase 5: Production Readiness (Week 5)\n\n- Performance optimization\n- Security hardening\n- Documentation completion\n- Production deployment\n\n## References\n\n- [Typer Documentation](https://typer.tiangolo.com/)\n- [Docker Python SDK](https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/)\n- [Kubernetes Python Client](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python)\n- [AgentRuntime CRD Specification](./deployment/client-go.md)\n- [Rich Documentation](https://rich.readthedocs.io/)\n\n## Appendix A: Complete Command Reference\n\n### publish Command Options\n\n| Option | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace`, `-f` | string | `.` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | string | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | string | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | string | `None` | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | string | `None` | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | string | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--region` | string | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | string | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--provider` | string | `agentcube` | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--node-port` | int | `None` | Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) |\n| `--replicas` | int | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n| `--namespace` | string | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n| `--verbose` | bool | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n## Appendix B: Example Workflows\n\n### Example 1: Publish to AgentCube with Local Image\n\n```bash\n# Build the agent\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /path/to/agent\n\n# Publish to AgentCube\nkubectl-agentcube publish \\\n  --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n  --image-url registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0 \\\n  --image-username myuser \\\n  --image-password mypass \\\n  --provider agentcube \\\n  --version v1.0.0\n```\n\n### Example 2: Publish to Kubernetes with Custom NodePort\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube publish \\\n  --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n  --provider k8s \\\n  --namespace production \\\n  --replicas 3 \\\n  --node-port 30080\n```\n\n### Example 3: Publish with Environment Variables\n\n```bash\nexport DOCKER_REGISTRY_URL=registry.example.com\nexport DOCKER_REGISTRY_USERNAME=myuser\nexport DOCKER_REGISTRY_PASSWORD=mypass\n\nkubectl-agentcube publish \\\n  --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n  --provider agentcube\n```\n\n## Appendix C: Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n\n#### 1. Docker Not Available\n\n**Error**: `RuntimeError: Docker is not available or not running`\n\n**Solution**:\n- Ensure Docker daemon is running\n- Check Docker service status: `systemctl status docker`\n- Verify user has Docker permissions\n\n#### 2. Registry Authentication Failed\n\n**Error**: `RegistryAuthenticationError: Failed to push image to registry`\n\n**Solution**:\n- Verify credentials are correct\n- Check registry URL format\n- Ensure user has push permissions\n\n#### 3. AgentRuntime Prerequisites Missing\n\n**Error**: `ValueError: router_url is required for agentcube provider`\n\n**Solution**:\n- Set `router_url` in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- Use `--router-url` flag (if supported)\n- Verify Router endpoint is accessible\n\n#### 4. Deployment Readiness Timeout\n\n**Error**: `TimeoutError: Deployment did not become ready within 120 seconds`\n\n**Solution**:\n- Check agent container logs: `kubectl logs <deployment-name>`\n- Verify readiness probe configuration\n- Check resource limits and quotas\n- Increase timeout if needed\n\n### Debug Mode\n\nEnable verbose logging for detailed troubleshooting:\n\n```bash\nkubectl-agentcube publish \\\n  --workspace /path/to/agent \\\n  --verbose\n```\n\nThis will show:\n- Detailed operation steps\n- API calls and responses\n- Error stack traces\n- Progress information","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775867783905,"end":1775867783915}}}}
